title: Super-Tsunami Tuesday Democratic primary/caucus delegate counts, USA by State, 2008
name: Super-Tsunami Tuesday Democratic primary/caucus delegate counts, USA by State, 2008
description: No time in the history have so many states held either a primary or a caucus on a single day. Nearly two dozen will hold the primary/caucus to vote for             the presidential candidates. Its a mini-general election, especially with the inclusion of California and New York who between them have a total of nearly 722 delegates, that is more than 1/3rd needed to win Democratic nomination. However, since Democrats allocate proportionate number of delegates based on the number of votes each presidential candidate gets, these rich set of delegates will be shared among the top tier candidates. The result of which is likely to be that the post-Super Tsunami Tuesday state will hold the key to who gets the nomination.      Delegate count source: http://politics.nytimes.com/election-guide/2008/primaries/democraticprimaries/index.html
